Death From Below! The Imperious Republican Democratic Autocratic Pneumatic Psychotic Syphilitic Hegemony spans many worlds and encompasses many races of humans, demi-humans, and aliens. One such species are the Space Dwarves, who, because of some kind of sci-fi pseudo-babble, are half the size and twice the man as most of the IRDAPPSH's average citizens. Those same conditions also gave them Scottish accents, uncomfortably thick beards, and a strange obsession with art deco, but whatever.

It could be said that the Space Dwarves are compensating for something by deploying their massive and rather phallic Mega-Cannon. However, it better be said quietly or far away from the ears of said Space Dwarves, else the speaker may find themselves learning to live without any legs, so be warned. The Mega-Cannon fires a shell the size of a cargo van at targets the Imperious Leader has determined to be "bothersome".

This product includes both 6mm and 8mm versions!

Another of the Space Dwarf's strange obsessions is building things HUGE, much larger than necessary. The Mjölnir Mobile Fortress is a huge armored crawler capable of carrying tanks, gyrocopters, and dozens of squat troops into battle. Armed with dozens of machine guns, antitank cannons, Gatling repeaters, anti-aircraft batteries, a siege mortar, and the patent-pending "Oh God Oh God We're All Gonna Die" siege cannon, which fires a slug the size of a Volkswagen, the Mjölnir can batter its way into any stronghold and wreak short, Scottish-accented havoc on the defenders within.

Note: This model is so big that I didn't bother making an 8mm version. It should work pretty well in both scales!

Prepare for the arrival of the Dread Forces of CHAOX! CHAOX is a faction of those who are torn between being exact copies of the Imperious Forces and being spiky emo Goth kids. This dichotomy puts them into a permanently violent mood, causing them to descend upon the Imperious worlds and wreak havoc. In the infamous Battle of Nowherius, CHAOX forces covertly swapped the Imperious Forces' regular coffee for decaf. The casualty count reached the low billions. Billions!

The CHAOX Hellifiknow is a ground-attack fighter built for one specific thing: killing tanks! Built around a wicked, heavy, tri-barrel, armor-piercing, plasma-core, sustainably-sourced, fair trade, dolphin-safe, hand-crafted artisanal autocannon, the Hellifiknow swoops down on enemy armor and rips it to pieces! As an added bonus, it looks damn sexy while doing it.

Note: This package includes both the classic 6mm/Epic scale and the newer 8mm/AT18 scale models!

Let's face it: Even in the far future, people are still obsessed with efficiency, doing more with less. So it is with maintaining the Imperious Leader's far-flung dominion, and the most efficient method of moving stuff is still the train. And when you have enemies, those trains make sweet, juicy targets, necessitating adding arms and armor to repel the bad guys.

This set includes not only nine different train cars, but compatible track segments. The various train cars have round guide lugs on the underside that serve to keep the cars centered on the tracks.

The GothiTech Armored Train includes:

- Armed Locomotive
- Flatbed Car
- Boxcar
- Tanker Car
- Passenger Car
- Nuclear Fuel Car
- Artillery Car (cannon prints separately and can be mounted up for firing or down for travel)
- Troop Car (includes mounting points for two turrets)
- Air Defense Car (includes two antiaircraft missile turrets)
- Five Track Segments (Straight Single, Curved Single, Y-Split, Straight Double, and Curved Double)
